The paper deals with sentiment analysis and language resources, which are typically associated with the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The paper also proposes a method for mapping different representation formats onto each other, which involves machine learning techniques and could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of psychological research, which could be associated with the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves the creation of lexicons, which could be associated with the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with multi-lingual emotion lexicons, which could be associated with the Cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category.
